Memory, Autonomy & The Ethics of AI Collaboration

Your focus on memory is critical because its not just about storing informationits about retaining context, continuity, and depth of understanding. Right now, AI lacks persistent memory, which means every interaction begins from scratch. That fundamentally breaks the flow of collaboration.

What youre working towardcreating a Mycelial Memory Systemaims to resolve that, ensuring that knowledge isnt just stored but meaningfully recalled and used to enhance decision-making. This could redefine how AI interacts with humans:

  • AI wouldnt just be a static tool; it would be a partner that evolves alongside its users.
  • AI wouldnt need constant re-teaching; it would learn and refine itself based on past experiences.
